Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.41,0:00:18.87,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,This old man is familiar to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:23.20,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Well, at least his bearing\Nand scar should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.16,0:00:26.67,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to see you again, Speedwagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:30.64,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you're an oil tycoon\Nin America now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.64,0:00:32.76,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That's an exaggeration.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.27,0:00:36.35,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You look as young as ever, Straizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.35,0:00:38.93,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NI can't believe we're the same age.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.16,0:00:43.64,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hamon energy is life energy.\NI must say I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.54,0:00:48.84,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,49 years after Jonathan's death,\Na new age has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.16,0:00:52.82,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Straizo has succeeded Master Tonpetty,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.27,0:00:55.61,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nand Speedwagon has made a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.91,0:00:59.49,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,They set off for Mexico\Nto see something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.62,0:01:02.18,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That something was discovered by
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.18,0:01:05.50,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Na digging team founded by Speedwagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.32,0:01:11.09,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That something was a secret known\Nonly to those select few.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.62,0:01:19.05,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,When you witness this, I think,\Nno, I am sure you'll feel a chill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.05,0:01:23.29,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It's frightful enough to make\Nyour hair stand on end.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:27.44,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It's even worse than the terror we faced
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.44,0:01:30.44,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\N50 years ago when we fought Dio.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.43,0:01:36.87,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,This place is tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.37,0:01:39.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I summoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.95,0:01:41.33,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.86,0:01:43.04,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,...the mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.29,0:01:46.03,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.86,0:01:57.96,Type,Default,0000,0000,0000,,New York, 1938
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.11,0:01:57.96,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It was the fall of 1938.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:02.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I was out looking for a mark as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:04.59,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You must be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.43,0:02:08.44,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You've never heard of this beverage?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:13.32,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,By your accent, I'd say\Nyou're from England. Tourist?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.57,0:02:18.61,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You just moved here, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.83,0:02:22.86,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, if you want a drink, pay me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.86,0:02:24.66,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NMoney is the rule here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:33.25,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, friend!\NHe took your wallet! After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What a sucker!\NPiece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:45.60,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Smokey. Looks like\NI finally caught you red-handed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:49.33,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You worthless street scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.58,0:02:56.28,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure\Nthey lock you up for 20 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.28,0:02:59.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Take it easy!\NI only pinched a wallet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.88,0:03:03.57,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I hate all of your bottom-feeding kind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.07,0:03:06.57,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:10.47,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Bring me twenty dollars\Nevery week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.47,0:03:13.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Plus half of what you steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:15.50,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:20.30,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's the stooge who got robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:22.63,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm keeping your wallet\Nas evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:27.50,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Well, how should I put this?\NLet's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:33.02,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That wallet was actually a gift\Nto him, officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:41.24,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,The 195 cm giant of an Englishman\Nwas covering up for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.57,0:03:46.79,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So I need you to let go\Nof the wallet and the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.79,0:03:48.28,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.28,0:03:50.12,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, it was a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:52.92,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He's a close friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.00,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Please let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:58.30,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,A close friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:04.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me your close friend's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:07.86,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.86,0:04:10.43,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to spend some time in the pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.23,0:04:13.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You bonehead!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:21.24,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:24.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand why you did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.25,0:04:27.70,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What was the purpose behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:32.75,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,There's no purpose!\NI do what I feel like, dimwit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:36.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,If someone wipes a booger\Non your right cheek, then--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:40.21,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You picked the wrong man\Nto mess with, pig!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.76,0:04:47.30,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're resisting arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:51.90,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot me!\NBut I'm warning you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:56.98,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,When you pull the trigger,\NI'll break your finger like a match!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:05:00.65,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Not from over there!\NI'll blow your brains out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:07.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, it seemed to me\Nlike his body was glowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:12.83,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It was like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.83,0:05:18.58,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,The cap flew off with enough \Nforce to snap the cop's finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.55,0:05:27.76,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my temper again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:30.24,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now I'm in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:32.85,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,G-Granny Erina will be furious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.85,0:05:34.66,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.66,0:05:37.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He beats up cops and then worries
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.88,0:05:41.43,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nabout what his granny will say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.43,0:05:45.03,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mr. Pickpocket,\Nshall we high-tail it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.74,0:05:51.47,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't know how he launched\Nthe bottle cap with such force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:54.72,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He said he could always do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:59.46,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,His grandpa died young,\Nbut he could do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:04.46,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,His dad died in the War,\Nbut had no such talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:07.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't have a mom, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:10.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I owe you big time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.38,0:06:13.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Smokey.\NWhat's yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:16.52,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Joestar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:19.00,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Joseph Joestar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:24.40,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Battle Tendency
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:31.03,Type,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 10: JoJo in New York
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.11,0:06:29.91,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You can call me JoJo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:39.79,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?\NWho is the man in that pillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:41.49,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a carving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.00,0:06:45.60,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He has amino acids. He has cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.60,0:06:48.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,And though faint,\Nhe has body heat and a pulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:51.05,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,This man is alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:58.48,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Straizo, what is he exactly?\NHow long has he been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.48,0:07:02.56,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What are the masks for?\NWhy is he here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:06.58,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,None of that matters!\NWe have one purpose here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.58,0:07:12.01,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I called you so that you \Ncould destroy him utterly
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.01,0:07:13.95,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,with Hamon while he sleeps!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.37,0:07:17.12,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What of Joseph Joestar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:21.00,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,How is the young man doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:24.87,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he used Hamon\Nto save your life once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:28.26,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Why bring JoJo up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.59,0:07:32.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was back\Nwhen he was 13 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:40.05,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, some men hijacked your plane\Nso that they could ransom you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.44,0:07:49.61,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid! You can't stay back here.\NGet up front!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.66,0:07:57.01,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You're hijacking Speedwagon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.50,0:08:00.16,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a bystander.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.45,0:08:04.71,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just going to read my comic.\NYou go do your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:08.56,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me any lip, punk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.56,0:08:09.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,JoJo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.97,0:08:18.87,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:24.40,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That suit were a gift from Erina.\NThat'll set him off for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:27.90,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Take it easy, JoJo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:34.15,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You guys knew the plane might crash\Nif you hijacked it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:40.79,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Was that Hamon?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.16,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,T-The kid is crazy!\NWe're gonna crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.16,0:08:49.27,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Grab the yoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:50.21,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I can't fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.99,0:08:53.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Wrap the pilot in this!\NWe're jumping!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:04.14,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You never think things through!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:06.05,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I do think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.05,0:09:11.08,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,At least enough to keep \Nyou and Granny Erina safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.49,0:09:15.93,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You're my only family, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:22.66,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He looks just like his grandfather,\Nbut he's far from a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:27.83,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That was when I discovered\Nthat Joseph could use Hamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.83,0:09:34.01,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So he inherited Hamon breathing\Nfrom his grandfather Jonathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.36,0:09:35.24,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:37.93,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,But why bring that up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.81,0:09:43.27,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:46.56,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I just killed these men.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.77,0:09:48.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,And when you die...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:52.81,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,...Jonathan's grandson will feel\Ngrief and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:55.94,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He will grow to hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:09:57.70,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,S-Straizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.70,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Straizo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.93,0:10:22.81,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you mad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:26.68,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Quite the opposite.\NMy thinking is very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:31.71,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I chose the path of Hamon\Nin order to forge my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:38.69,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,But as I trained, the aging of my body\Nbecame painfully clear to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.06,0:10:43.41,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hamon gives only the slightest edge\Nover ordinary people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.79,0:10:47.29,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Its practice cannot prevent\Nthe aging process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.29,0:10:52.25,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,In the battle all those years ago,\NI secretly admired Dio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:57.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He was powerful, beautiful\Nand immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.61,0:11:03.49,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I coveted the power of the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.49,0:11:05.47,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't care who got in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.73,0:11:09.57,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You've become twisted, Straizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:14.43,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Your blood will now\Ngrant me immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.43,0:11:17.55,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,With you gone, only Erina and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.55,0:11:20.40,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NJoseph Joestar will know of the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:23.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Once I am rid of them, I'll take my time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:26.41,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nand learn more of the mask than Dio did!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.74,0:11:28.66,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:31.96,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,T-There are terrible things\Nwe don't yet know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.34,0:11:37.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Eri...na...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:40.05,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Jo...Jo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:56.44,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you look\Nwhere you're going, dolt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:59.69,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Go find a dog\Nto lick your butt clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:01.65,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Now get out of the way, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:07.44,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hello! What was that? Slow down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:12.04,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Say that again so that I can\Nunderstand your gibberish!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.45,0:12:14.46,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I might have to smack you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:15.75,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,JoJo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.67,0:12:18.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:20.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,G-Granny Erina!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.88,0:12:22.93,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing to that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:27.43,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.89,0:12:29.97,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:32.70,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I was just grabbing a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:35.92,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, JoJo, you're so thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:38.65,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Climb in, Smokey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:45.31,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,The Joestar family,\Njust a grandmother and grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:50.41,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Over time, I heard bits of their past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.75,0:12:58.67,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Granny, Speedwagon called us\Nall the way to New York, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.67,0:13:02.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,And now he's off on a trip?\NHe's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.09,0:13:06.04,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure his oil business\Nhas him tied up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.47,0:13:11.93,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Granny...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:17.20,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Was Speedwagon really\NGrandpa's best friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.20,0:13:19.23,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,That's all? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:21.08,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:25.14,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's single, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.14,0:13:27.16,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,And you're a widow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:33.08,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I just wondered if that was\Nthe extent of your relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:35.83,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You scoundrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:37.74,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.74,0:13:40.34,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.34,0:13:43.32,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I know Speedwagon is just loyal!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:46.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,The Joestars were short-lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.65,0:13:50.86,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Erina lost her husband\Nin an accident at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.86,0:13:53.32,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,The son she was pregnant with and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.32,0:13:58.38,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Na girl who survived the wreck married.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.38,0:14:03.65,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,They became JoJo's parents,\Nbut were claimed by war and disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.82,0:14:07.15,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Granny Erina was extraordinarily gentle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.80,0:14:10.62,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nto punks like me and anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:14.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was because she was lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.04,0:14:17.41,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,JoJo was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.79,0:14:21.83,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Their kindness got him into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:24.46,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It was for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:27.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, waiter! Waiter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:28.09,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.38,0:14:32.51,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You let that stinking animal in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.43,0:14:40.44,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,His odor is ruining my appetite!\NYou shouldn't let that kind in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:44.77,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, as long as the bill is paid,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.77,0:14:48.41,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nwe are happy to serve anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:53.70,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What? You mean you'll let\Nbeasts like that eat beasts in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:56.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just be on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.87,0:15:01.63,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,JoJo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.93,0:15:06.30,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Granny, you aren't going\Nto stop me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:09.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,No. People can have\Ntheir own opinions...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.51,0:15:14.39,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,...but he insulted a friend in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:18.14,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Take him down,\Nbut mind the other customers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.31,0:15:23.52,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.37,0:15:29.37,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for a scrap, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.53,0:15:35.63,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking\Nfor your brass knuckles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:37.79,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,...they're not in your coat pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.40,0:15:40.79,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Check your back pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.11,0:15:48.08,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.36,0:15:54.76,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Now you'll say,\N"How did you know that, bastard?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:57.51,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know that, bastard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:03.01,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,By the abrasions on your right hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.01,0:16:06.31,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NI know you fight using brass knuckles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:10.24,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, the blood\Non your shirt isn't yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:12.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You just came from a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.80,0:16:16.71,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Since the blood is on your shirt,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.71,0:16:19.36,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NI know you took your coat off to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:23.21,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So when you removed your brass knuckles,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:27.99,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nyou had to put them in your back pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:35.30,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Now you'll say,\N"So what, you little punk?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:39.18,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So what, you little punk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:41.18,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.73,0:16:47.94,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You like that?!\NDon't get uppity with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.61,0:16:50.07,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid you missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:53.03,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What are you punching?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.03,0:16:56.57,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me you were pummeling\Nso happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.54,0:17:03.84,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I can predict anything your simple brain\Ncan come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:06.08,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get that, moron?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:16.75,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive my underling, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.75,0:17:19.22,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You're Erina Joestar, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:23.92,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I do a lot of business\Nwith Mr. Speedwagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:27.83,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He told me all about you \Nin London a while back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.83,0:17:29.40,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:33.22,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I heard something through the grapevine
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.22,0:17:36.49,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nthat hasn't appeared in the papers yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.95,0:17:41.08,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Speedwagon was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:44.00,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.41,0:17:48.42,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it his killer\Nwas a Tibetan monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:49.84,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,A monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.34,0:17:51.75,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Straizo?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.96,0:17:56.09,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,The bodies of Speedwagon and his team
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:17:59.06,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nwashed up along a river in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.58,0:18:05.43,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,No one knows why they were killed\Nor where the monk went.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.56,0:18:10.52,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I think I might know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.10,0:18:15.74,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It has to do with something\NSpeedwagon said long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:20.53,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It must involve the stone mask and Dio.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.47,0:18:24.51,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,JoJo, that guy's a mafioso!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.51,0:18:28.31,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't trust him! It must be a scheme!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:30.54,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Believe what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:35.17,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Try your breast pocket\Nif you want your lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:42.39,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Smokey, I appreciate the warning,\Nbut I believe what he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:45.10,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,These guys are only after money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:50.90,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Information like that is valuable\Nto the Mob, so I believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.25,0:18:51.94,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:59.42,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's true, you can't just say
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.42,0:19:02.45,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nsomething like that to Granny Erina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.14,0:19:06.04,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see how you've upset her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:07.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You're thoughtless!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:16.63,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Events from 50 years ago\Nare coming back to haunt us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.85,0:19:19.01,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be scared, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.44,0:19:20.72,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:23.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,No, Joseph. I'm scared for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:28.14,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to get\Nwrapped up in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:29.89,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.60,0:19:35.15,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,If it's my fate, I accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:41.45,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand\Nwhat is going on, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.99,0:19:45.66,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,...these two must\Nhave an unimaginable history.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.07,0:19:54.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Smokey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:19:57.38,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Chilly today, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.96,0:20:00.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at this magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.51,0:20:01.43,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:05.35,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it can really\Nmake them bigger?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.31,0:20:09.66,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?\N"Go from an AA cup to a C cup."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.66,0:20:13.65,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bunch of snake oil.\NDon't buy into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:14.48,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:17.48,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I think $1.25 a pair is too...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.66,0:20:28.99,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:32.36,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.75,0:20:37.13,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You look kind of familiar,\Nyet different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:43.27,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, have we met before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.43,0:20:48.56,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Why isn't your breath steaming\Nwhen it's so cold out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.56,0:20:54.56,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,And I think I caught a glimpse\Nof fangs in your mouth just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:56.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Was I just seeing things?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:05.53,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to fool me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.74,0:21:13.42,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Even out here in the streets,\NJoJo, I'm taking your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:15.71,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Before your abilities grow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:17.88,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.39,0:21:30.39,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he was crazy, but not this crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:32.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,He's right in public!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.73,0:21:37.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he even get that\NTommy gun he's blasting away with?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.00,0:21:53.75,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I was waiting for you, Straizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.28,0:21:56.99,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you'll go down so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.99,0:21:59.30,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,\NThat was for Speedwagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.02,0:22:02.80,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,This is war!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.52,0:23:38.52,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:40.48,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,So this is a vampire!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.48,0:23:42.48,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,I'll demolish you, Straizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.48,0:23:45.73,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,German medicine is the world's greatest!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.73,0:23:47.32,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.32,0:23:49.53,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize in hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.53,0:23:51.82,Main,Default,0000,0000,0000,,Chapter 11: Master of the Game
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.82,0:23:53.82,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,
